  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\n\n---\n## Issue\n\nThe web3 global variable is initialized too late, on page load event, after the angularjs application is already initialized and after the first rendering,  so it's not available inside a controller code.\nThis behaviour started at commit 9003a2ab70040da06e269254e9fdadd228f025c5 with truffle-default-builder module version 1.0.2, before this release the web3 was already initialized at controller code execution.\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\nUse this project: https://github.com/mpolci/truffle-web3-lazy-initialization\nrun testrpc, then:\n\n```\ntruffle migrate\ntruffle serve\n```\n\nthen open http://localhost:8080\n## Expected Behavior\n\nthe web page should report the following messages:\n\n```\ninside controller initialization\nwindow.web3 variable initialized: true\ncurrenteProvider initialized: true\n\nduring rendering\nwindow.web3 variable initialized: true\ncurrenteProvider initialized: true\n```\n## Actual Results\n\n```\ninside controller initialization\nwindow.web3 variable initialized: false\ncurrenteProvider initialized: false\n\nduring rendering\nwindow.web3 variable initialized: true\ncurrenteProvider initialized: true\n```\n## Environment\n- Operating System: ubuntu 16.04\n- Truffle version: 2.0.8\n- Ethereum client: testrpc\n- node version: 6.5.0\n- npm version: 3.10.7\n",
