    "body": "FYI; I had this as well and solved it in the angular controller by postponing everything that needed web3 (like loading accounts) to after document ready:\n\n```\napp.controller('indexController', function($scope, web3Service) {\n\nvar init = () => {\n    web3Service.getAccounts().then(function (accs) {\n        $scope.accounts = accs;\n    }, function(err) {\n        console.log(err);\n    });\n\n};\n\nangular.element(document).ready(function () {\n    init();\n});\n```\n",
